    "title": "Capacity Alert Monitoring",
    "description": "Critical capacity alerts are promptly investigated and addressed in line with the incident handling procedure.",
    "principle": "The entity maintains, monitors, and evaluates current processing capacity and use of system components (infrastructure, data, and software) to manage capacity demand and to enable the implementation of additional capacity to help meet its objectives.",
    "category": "Availability",
    "status": "Mapped",
    "owner": "Security",
    "frequency": "Ongoing",
    "evidenceType": "Policy document",
    "criteria": [
      "A1.1"
    ],
    "focus": "A1.1 - Availability\nThe entity maintains, monitors, and evaluates current processing capacity and use of system components (infrastructure, data, and software) to manage capacity demand and to enable the implementation of additional capacity to help meet its objectives.\n\nPoints of Focus:\n\nMeasures Current Usage - The use of the system components is measured to establish a baseline for capacity management and to use when monitoring and evaluating the risk of impaired availability due to capacity constraints. Forecasts Capacity - The expected average and peak use of system components is forecasted and compared to system capacity and associated tolerances. Forecasting considers system resilience and capacity in the event of the failure of system components that constrain capacity. Makes Changes Based on Forecasts - The system change management process is initiated when forecasted usage exceeds capacity tolerances."
